Many smartphones come with built-in FM chips but do not have the feature activated . 
  Broadcasters are pushing for the mobile industry to activate the FM chips within smartphones . 
  Norway has become the first country to switch off its FM radio service in 2017 . 
  Apple’s iPhones, Samsung‘s Galaxy phones and LG phones all have FM chips . 
  But nearly two thirds of smartphones don’t have FM radio activated . 
  Many mobile network providers are reluctant to allow the feature . 
 